I was just used to great ensembles performing sacred and secular music of the Middle Age... but never before I had listened to an A Cappella Quartet with women only. And believe me, it's really worth to listen to... just imagine the haunting and weird medieval modes sung with the high pitch of female voices... No surprise if you start looking around expecting angels to show. 

For lovers of ancient music. :)

There are 21 albums: 17 from their discography (pretty complete apart a 2010 carols album which was nowhere to be found) and 4 included in a single Christmas box.
The sampling rate is 320kbps. (Except for the A Portrait of Anonymous 4 compilation) 

Enjoy :)


